# Sleep Disorders

Educational notes on sleep disorders, aimed at clinicians, residents, and students interested in mental health.

## Purpose
- Provide a structured overview of common sleep disorders
- Support clinical reasoning and differential diagnosis
- Offer concise, practical content in Portuguese

## Planned subtopics
- Insomnia and its clinical profiles
- Circadian rhythm disorders
- Hypersomnias and excessive daytime sleepiness
- Parasomnias
- Sleep and psychiatric comorbidities
- General principles of sleep hygiene

> Note: Content in this repository is for educational purposes only and does not replace formal clinical training, local protocols, or individualized medical care.
